I just completed my very first SAG voiceover project! 🥺 

It was a small role but was so excited I had to take a celebratory selfie. So very thankful for the opportunities I get every year and slowly working my way to upgrade the little home studio. (This is where I work on all my songs too btw - in our basement/bedroom! 😁) 

I hope to create a better sounding experience when we move out! 💖

How many people can say that they are “living the dream”? 💭

10 years ago, when I committed myself to acting, I didn’t realize how eye opening of a journey it was to my humanity. 

Today, I am not some big star in the theaters (yet!) But I get to spend my days with inspiring, talented people. I get to experience the stories that my friends and new acquaintances have labored for many years to write and produce. I get to experience alternate lives and universes through the work I create. I get to learn and practice a new skill everyday. I get the opportunity to be a vehicle for someone else’s dreams who might even be bigger than mine.

All the while, I have learned not to chain myself to the title of the “actor” which has allowed me to cultivate the meaningful experiences every human should have in every stage of life. This craft has forced me to practice gratitude everyday. So yes, I can say that right now, I truly am “living the dream”. ✨

When I look at this photo, my heart wells up with joy to see all the possibilities we can create together, and I am so excited to learn more about each and every one of you. 🥲 Am I being too sentimental? Ok, let me just go back to being a gremlin.

Thank you @yesthatdavidpark and @exemplarpictures for thinking of me for Titans: Oblivion! LET’S MAKE THIS HAPPEN! 🎬🎥

Bless the algorithm for letting me do more voice acting challenges like these until I can improve my home studio. 🥹💖 This was so much fun! This is a duet with voice actress of Neon from Valorant @vanillevela ! 

#voiceacting #voiceactor #voiceoverartist

Last weekend, I had the opportunity to watch and co-host “Daughters of Monster Magnet”‘s (@daughtersofmonstermagnet) live premiere and it was a film to behold! Thank you to my friends who were able to make it to the screening!

It took me some time to reflect on the film and what impact being a part of this production made on me.

Metaphor upon metaphor, I left the screening confused about the deep emotions welling up in me. Since this was my first time watching it, there were many things I didn’t understand. Yet, the human heart understood it all too well. 

Strange how we can still decipher meaning of things we don’t completely understand?

The feelings of loneliness and grief, the whirlwind of circumstances that shape our lives, what we do and experience that doesn’t make sense to others or even ourselves, how the only way to move forward is taking the time to reflect on the past, present, and future, and look beyond the physical realm to be a part of something much bigger than ourselves…

Lili, in the film, quite literally goes through all these phases with the help of the mysterious and elusive psychonaut who has been visiting her throughout her lifetime. The gift of Monster Magnet was a gruesome yet beautiful one that allowed Lili to travel between different dimensions and see what has become of her and her mother. This gift paved way of who she will soon become. 

The question by the end of this film becomes: What now?

It’s a question we all ask ourselves.

DMM is a unique and surreal coming-of-age film that shows while we may not have control over the circumstances that shape who we are, life gives us the opportunity to use our tragedies to fuel whatever mission has been handed down to us. We just have to discover our own psychonauts to take that next step.

Thank you Kosaku (@psychonaut_lili), Jiyeon (@berry_kombu_cha), and Kiyoko for giving me the opportunity to be a part of this wonderful production and a big congrats to the rest of cast and crew who worked so hard in making this film possible! 💖

I can’t believe we’re already in the other half of 2023! I’ve taken more effort in romanticizing the small things in life. 🥀

Recently, I’ve been decorating and cleaning our new apartment so the hubby and I fall in love with being in our own space. 💖

I haven’t been able to make new friends up here yet since moving costs and medical bills eat up most of my $$$ and free time so I’ve been streaming to fill up my social battery instead. 

Despite that, I’m so thankful that my business has stayed consistent this entire year and for the friends that still connect with me online. 

I thought that acting work would be dead for me this year because of the move (and the ongoing strike that has been affecting the entire industry) but I was able to be involved in quite a few small productions despite the transition. 

With all the wars, calamities, and new changes happening to the world, I can only have nothing but gratitude for the situation I’m in. Right now, a lot of my focus has been my own growth and self-development but I hope that one day I feel secure enough in myself and abilities that I can contribute more to others.

As always, to my friends and colleagues, thank you for continuously thinking of involving me in your projects. It’s always an honor for me to serve your story with whatever talents God has allowed me to develop.

Maybe it’s just me getting old but I’m beginning to make peace with the pace of whatever stage of life I’m in. 🫠

Who are these crazy people who shot a 48-hour film a day after the NYC floods?! 🤪 Just got home from the screening and I’m SO proud of everyone for making such a solid film in a short amount of time.

Lots of memories on this with @thisisjennalam creating the screenplay the night before. Me literally learning the story the day of. Collaborating and rehearsing with @chrispinofficial in lil silly ways to get the right chemistry on camera. Unexpectedly meeting @sokheanjouk for the first time after talking with him online for over a year… and so many more. 😩💖

Super happy to be on this new adventure and meeting some NYC artists here! 😁 LET’S GO LIGHTING LAMS.

Celebrating some of my most recent self tapes! 💖 I realized I’ve been taking them for granted and that each one I receive is a milestone - a blessing of opportunity.

2023 was truly a year of emotional and spiritual breakthroughs for me.

I’m going to make 2024 the year of taking action without letting the past and the traumas holding me back! 🙏 LET’S GO!

#actorslife #actorsjourney #asianactor #asianactress

Happy New Year! 🎊🍾 

I’m actually so glad I made this reel because it captured a lot of the beautiful moments I’ve experienced in 2023. 

I think we (i.e. me lol) tend to put too much focus on all the negative feelings and the limbo periods during our downtime that we sometimes forget how colorful our world really is.

I want 2024 to be less focused on achievements and more focused on the journey, process, memories, and friends we make along the way. Anything else is beyond our control. 

Let’s allow our accomplishments to be the icing on the cake we call “life”. Even without the icing, the cake is still delicious.

Here’s to a new year of building a well-rounded and more fulfilling life that makes room for love and physical/mental/spiritual/creative growth. 💖

(Also this template didn’t have enough media slots because I didn’t even get to share my experience in New Mexico. 😭)
